    "The Cross Ambiguity Function (CAF), which represents the correlation between y[n] and the spreading code of the i-th satellite at a specific delay/Doppler pair in discrete time, encodes this correlation operation, as illustrated in the equation as follows:which can be expressed more compactly in vector notation after gathering N samples from the samples and the local code as y,c i ∈ C N ×1 as C i (τ, f d) = c H i yN.",
